The paper deals with the performance analysis of the MUSIC algorithm for spectral estimation, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The multidimensional aspect of the problem suggests that it could also be relevant to the statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities.
